      "author": "nauppece",
      "description": "Security hardening + configurability.\n\n- Harden vault writes against semi-trusted window titles (a crafted browser tab title can no longer corrupt the day's session block or the note's YAML properties).\n- Daily-note heading is now configurable (Settings → Daily-note heading); empty = append at end of file.\n- Default data folder is now \"TimeMeter\" (existing installs keep their setting).\n- Verified no command/AppleScript injection (execFile, static args), no network, no secrets.\n\nManual install: put main.js, manifest.json, styles.css into <vault>/.obsidian/plugins/timemeter/ and enable in Community plugins.",
